    • Constructor Detail

      • KurentoTreeAPI

        public KurentoTreeAPI(LooperExecutor executor,
                      java.lang.String uri,
                      TreeListener listener)
        Constructor that initializes required instances and parameters for the API calls. WebSocket connections are not established in the constructor. User is responsible for opening, closing and checking if the connection is open through the corresponding API calls.
        Parameters:
        executor - is the asynchronous UI-safe executor for tasks.
        uri - is the web socket link to the tree web services.
        listener - interface handles the callbacks for responses, notifications and errors.

    • Method Detail

      • sendCreateTree

        public void sendCreateTree(java.lang.String treeId,
                           int id)
        The method represents client's request to create a new tree in Tree server. The response contains attributes "value" and "sessionId", where value is the name of the created tree.
        Parameters:
        treeId - is the name of the tree to be created.
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendSetTreeSource

        public void sendSetTreeSource(java.lang.String treeId,
                              java.lang.String offerSdp,
                              int id)
        The method represents a request to configure the emitter (source) in a broadcast session (tree). The response contains attributes "sdpAnswer" and "sessionId".
        Parameters:
        treeId - is the name of the tree this method refers to.
        offerSdp - is the SDP offer sent by this client.
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendAddIceCandidate

        public void sendAddIceCandidate(java.lang.String treeId,
                                java.lang.String sinkId,
                                java.lang.String sdpMid,
                                int sdpMLineIndex,
                                java.lang.String candidate,
                                int id)
        The method to request to add a new ice candidate. The response includes the following parameters: sessionId
        Parameters:
        treeId - is the name of the tree this method refers to.
        sinkId - is the name of the previously connected sink.
        sdpMid - is the media stream identification, "audio" or "video", for the m-line.
        sdpMLineIndex - is the index (starting at 0) of the m-line in the SDP
        candidate - contains the candidate attribute information
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.
